article.headline: Southern Miss. 86, William Carey 60
article.story: HATTIESBURG, Miss. (AP) -- Southern Miss used a big first-half run to break open a close game and never looked back in defeating crosstown foe William Carey 86-60 Tuesday night. Jeremy Wise converted 9-of-19 shots from the floor, including a 3-pointer and a free throw, to score a team-high 20 points to go along with seven assists, while Courtney Beasley added 17 and R.L. Horton tallied 14. Down 14-10 early in the opening half, Southern Miss scored the next 12 points as Sai'Quon Stone hit two straight baskets during the run and extended the lead to as much as 15, taking a 36-21 advantage into intermission. The Crusaders, which got a game-high 26 points from Southern Miss transfer Kyle LaMonte, tried to keep the game close in the second half on 3-point shots. William Carey hit 5-of-11 3-pointers in the second half (45.5 percent). Dexter Cheairs hit 4-of-7 long-range jumpers to add 16 for the Crusaders. Still, the Golden Eagles took advantage of 19 turnovers, outscoring the Crusaders 28-2 off the opponent's miscues.
